Date: 0/0/1958
Source: Farm Engineering
Author: RIDDOLLS
Vol / Page: 410
Edition:
Quote: Stays should never be less than 9 ft. long , and are usually 10 ft. If the resultant pull is slightly below the centre of the stay, and so does not tend to tilt the strainer over at the top.
